{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"diskInject","kind":"identifier"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"kind":"content","content":[{"anchor":"discussion","type":"heading","level":2,"text":"Discussion"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The script runs automatically when macOS starts — no SSH,"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"no agent, no network, and no manual setup required. This is"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"the only provisioning mode that works on a completely vanilla"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"macOS installation from an IPSW.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How it works:"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" Before the VM boots, Spooktacular mounts"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"the guest’s data volume on the host and writes a standard"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"macOS LaunchDaemon that executes your script at boot time."}]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Best for:"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Fresh VMs created from IPSW where you need"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"zero-touch automation — CI runners, test environments,"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"automated fleet provisioning.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"Requires:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" Nothing in the guest. Works with any macOS."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"roleHeading":"Case","symbolKind":"case","title":"ProvisioningMode.diskInject","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}],"fragments":[{"text":"case","kind":"keyword"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"text":"diskInject","kind":"identifier"}],"role":"symbol","externalID